The paper deals with algorithms for testing and estimating statistical properties of distributions, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on k-modal distributions over a discrete domain, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of reductions as a main conceptual contribution suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the focus on testing and estimating statistical properties suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-category statistics (cs.SI).
